yingyinNormal.en: This is unexpected, LOS. Communication lost. Standby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可是意料之外，通讯丢失，待命。

yingyinNormal.en: No. No, nothing so obvious. We need someone thoroughly unexpected.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，不能这么明显，我们需要一个完全意想不到的人。

yingyinNormal.en: And for a scandal to really blow up, all it needs is an unexpected turn.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要想丑闻完全的暴光，需要的只是一个偶然的转折点。

yingyinNormal.en: Would anyone else in the group like to speak to that? Hazel? Unexpected.
yingyinNormal.zh: 小组中有谁想聊聊这个话题的吗？海蓁？出乎意料啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Who knows, tonight I could do too much heroin and die an unexpected death.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天晓得我今晚会不会因为嗑药过多而突然暴毙了呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Last night, I experienced something new, an extraordinary meal from a singularly unexpected source.
yingyinNormal.zh: 昨晚我有个全新的体验，一顿奇妙的菜肴来自令人意想不到的出处!

yingyinNormal.en: Then one night, an unexpected intruder arrived at the castle, seeking shelter from the bitter storm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个风雨交加的夜晚，一位不速之客进入了城堡，想要避雨。

yingyinNormal.en: This is unexpected. I've bought your parents cinema tickets and Granddad's in his room. Asleep, I think.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还真是意外。我给你爸妈买了电影票，你爷爷也在他自己房间，应该睡着了。

yingyinNormal.en: And there is one other perhaps unexpected ingredient for my version of this classic British loaf. Olive oil.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许还有一种意想不到的配料，在我做的传统英式面包里，那就是橄榄油。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, things took an unexpected turn. Yes. He went back on his deal, because he's as pliable as his testimony.
yingyinNormal.zh: 事情出现了意外变化。对，他违背了协议，因为他和自己的证词一样不可靠。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, Mrs Norbury, I must admit this is unexpected. Vivian Norbury, who out-smarted them all. All except Sherlock Holmes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 诺伯里太太，我得承认这我没想到。薇薇安·诺伯里，比所有人都聪明，除了夏洛克·福尔摩斯。

yingyinNormal.en: But it'll be in an odd phrase in an on-line blog, or an unexpected trip to the countryside, or a misplaced lonely hearts ad. Your move!
yingyinNormal.zh: 答案也许是网上博客一处奇怪用词，一次临时乡间旅行，或者发错地方的征友广告。该你走了!
